{{Infobox baseball biography |name=Dwayne Henry |position=[[Pitcher]] |image= |bats=Right |throws=Right |birth_date={{birth date and age|1962|2|16}} |birth_place=[[Elkton, Maryland]] |debutleague = MLB |debutdate=September 7 |debutyear=1984 |debutteam=[[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]] |finalleague = MLB |finaldate=September 30 |finalyear=1995 |finalteam=[[Detroit Tigers]] |statleague = MLB |stat1label=[[Win (baseball)|Win-Loss record]] |stat1value=14-15 |stat2label=[[Earned run average]] |stat2value=4.65 |stat3label=[[Strikeout]]s |stat3value=275 |teams= *[[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]] ({{by|1984}}–{{by|1988}}) *[[Atlanta Braves]] ({{by|1989}}–{{by|1990}}) *[[Houston Astros]] ({{by|1991}}) *[[Cincinnati Reds]] ({{by|1992}}–{{by|1993}}) *[[Seattle Mariners]] ({{by|1993}}) *[[Chunichi Dragons]] ({{by|1994}}) ([[Nippon Professional Baseball|NPB]]) *[[Detroit Tigers]] ({{by|1995}}) }} '''Dwayne Allen Henry''' (born February 16, 1962 in [[Elkton, Maryland]]) is a former [[Major League Baseball]] [[relief pitcher]] who played for the [[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]], Atlanta Braves, [[Houston Astros]], [[Cincinnati Reds]], [[Seattle Mariners]] and [[Detroit Tigers]]. In {{by|1994}}, he pitched in Japan for the [[Chunichi Dragons]].
Henry made his major league debut on September 7, {{mlby|1984}}, after being drafted in the second round of the [[1980 Major League Baseball Draft]]. His career ended when the Tigers released him on October 12, {{mlby|1995}}.
